properties.description: The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: (Required) The unique name to assign to the data bag. This is the name that other server clients will use to find and retrieve data from the data bag.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: data_bag_name
properties.description: (Required) The name of the data bag into which this item will be placed.

properties.name: content_json
properties.description: (Required) A string containing a JSON object that will be the content of the item. Must at minimum contain a property called "id" that is unique within the data bag, which will become the identifier of the created item.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: (Required) The unique name to assign to the environment. This name will be used when nodes are created within the environment.

properties.name: description
properties.description: (Optional) A human-friendly description of the environment. If not set, a placeholder of "Managed by Terraform" will be set.

properties.name: default_attributes_json
properties.description: (Optional) String containing a JSON-serialized object containing the default attributes for the environment.

properties.name: override_attributes_json
properties.description: (Optional) String containing a JSON-serialized object containing the override attributes for the environment.

properties.name: cookbook_constraints
properties.description: (Optional) Mapping of cookbook names to cookbook version constraints that should apply for this environment.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: (Required) The unique name to assign to the node.

properties.name: environment_name
properties.description: - (Optional) the nodes environment name (default: _default)

properties.name: automatic_attributes_json
properties.description: (Optional) String containing a JSON-serialized object containing the automatic attributes for the node.

properties.name: normal_attributes_json
properties.description: (Optional) String containing a JSON-serialized object containing the normal attributes for the node.

properties.name: default_attributes_json
properties.description: (Optional) String containing a JSON-serialized object containing the default attributes for the node.

properties.name: override_attributes_json
properties.description: (Optional) String containing a JSON-serialized object containing the override attributes for the node.

properties.name: run_list
properties.description: (Optional) List of strings to set as the run list for the node.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: (Required) The unique name to assign to the role.

properties.name: description
properties.description: (Optional) A human-friendly description of the role. If not set, a placeholder of "Managed by Terraform" will be set.

properties.name: default_attributes_json
properties.description: (Optional) String containing a JSON-serialized object containing the default attributes for the role.

properties.name: override_attributes_json
properties.description: (Optional) String containing a JSON-serialized object containing the override attributes for the role.

properties.name: run_list
properties.description: (Optional) List of strings to set as the run list for any nodes that belong to this role.
